    <h1>UWP Speech recognition app on Windows 10 IoT on raspberry pi controlling the lights and sending data to cloud</h1>
    <p>
        This was actually a rather small project, but I decided to mention it cause it was a lot of fun. We created it for our IoT classes on university. Also it has a lot of buzzwords.
    </p>
    <p>
        Basically, I installed windows 10 IoT on Raspberry Pi, connected external sound card, then connected external microphone to the sound card.
    </p>
    <p>
        Then I was able to use windows speech recognition API in UWP project, and control the lights based on sound command. I've also setup sending the information about registered words to IoT Event Hub on Azure.
